	<br/>
	<%=link_to(image_tag("/screenshots/dashboard1_small.png"), "/screenshots/dashboard1.png", :rel=>"facebox")%>
</div>
<br/><br/>
<h1>Todo List</h1>
Your Todo list is a singular list of todo items that you specify. Why is it singular? You can read this <a href="http://lifehelpr.wordpress.com/2010/10/29/todos-vs-lists/" target="blank">blog post</a> to find out why.
<br/><br/>
You can categorize Todo items and filter by category to view things that just pertain to a specific category you care about at the moment.
<br/><br/>
Further more, you will notice "archived items". We auto archive all of your todos that have been marked complete for over an hour. We do this so that your current working todo list stays fresh and clean. If you want to resurrect something from the archive, you simply mark it undone and it will pop back in to your working todo list.
<div class="center">
	<br/>
	<%=link_to(image_tag("/screenshots/todo_list1_small.png"), "/screenshots/todo_list1.png", :rel=>"facebox")%>
</div>
<br/><br/>
<h1>Adding a Todo Item</h1>
When you add a new Todo Item, the only required field is the Name. You don't have to provide anything else. Everything else is optional. 
<br/><br/>
The Due Date and how reminders work is something we get confusion on. When you set a Due Date, magic happens. As your item gets closer to the date it is due, you will notice it will climb up your list in priority automatically. The day your item is due, we will mark it as overdue and start sending you reminders on the reminder schedule you set on your settings page. You will get reminders at the times of day you have set until the item is marked complete or its due date is changed.
