<h1>Settings</h1>
Your settings page is everything you need to control your experience on LifeHelpr.com. This is where you control what emails you want to receive, what your reminder schedule is, and even where you change your email address or password.
<br/><br/>
<h2>SMS reminders</h2>
You can elect to set reminders to be sent via SMS. When you put in your mobile number and carrier, we will send you an SMS with an activation code. You must return to the page with your activation code and put that in the box that appears and click save to activate your phone. Once activated, you will be able to select SMS related options for reminders. Just remember that standard text rates apply.
<br/><br/>
<h2>Reminders</h2>
Some confusion arises when users try to setup reminders. Since Todo Items aren't bound to a specific time of day (you would use a calendar for that), we use abstract times for reminders. After much research we have found that almost everyone has specific times of the day that they are most likely to be able to take care of things they have forgotten about. If you think about what times of the day are best for you and put those times as your reminder times, you will find that things tend to get done. What we are doing is allowing you to work your reminders in to your schedule. So when an item is due, you will start receiving reminders for those items at these times.

